Metlife opens Botswana branch office . South Africa insurer Metropolitan Life announced on Monday that it had opened a Botswana branch office in Gaborone . Metlife is in partnership with the Botswana Development Corporation ( BDC ) which holds 25 percent of the equity of Metropolitan Life of Botswana Ltd . Speaking at the launch of the company , Minister for Commerce and Industry George Kgoroba , representing the Vice - president and Minister for Finance and Development Planning Festus Mogae , welcomed " the breaking of an insurance monopoly " in Botswana . Botswana Insurance , a partnership between South African group African Life Assurance and Canadian company St Paul , had been the only life assurer in the country . Metlife has trained and accredited seven Botswana brokers , who will initially operate under the control of Metlife in South Africa . 
